questionContent.body: A boy walks 10 meters east, turns left and walks 6 meters, turns left again and walks 10 meters. How far and in what direction is he from his starting point?

solution.name: Solution 1
solution.details:
The boy walks 10 meters east → now 10m east of start.

Turns left → now facing north, walks 6 meters.

Turns left again → now facing west, walks 10 meters back.

So, he ends up 6 meters north of the starting point.

His east-west movement cancels out (10 east − 10 west = 0).

Final answer: 6 meters away, in the **north** direction.
